Plan update
The main issue looks runtime-related: the current contract evaluates round counts statefully, so later attempts can erase earlier profits instead of preserving the best executable path. I’m switching to isolated per-route/per-round executors so the best profitable candidate is actually retained.
  ✓ Inspect PoC and nearby tests
  ✓ Diagnose failing profit path
  → Patch `src/FlawVerifier.sol`
  • Run focused Forge test
